added.title: The Other Side: The Tournament
added.description: The Tournament - Hoping to win a special prize for his Dad's birthday, Craig and his friends compete in a tournament on the Other Side of the Creek!

added.title: Creek Shorts
added.description: Craig and his friends demonstrate How to Map the Creek, Craig tries to name every Creek Kid, and more! The Williams Family Intro: Craig imagines what it would be like if his family had a TV Show./How to Map the Creek: Craig shows us how to map the Creek!/Brother Chauffeur: Craig gets to be the ultimate backseat driver./The Kids in the Creek: Craig tries to name every kid in the Creek, but it's easier said than done./Between A Rock: Craig and his friends run afoul of the rock kids.

added.title: The Ground Is Lava!
added.description: When an intense game of "The Ground is Lava" breaks out, Craig must carefully traverse the Creek to save his sister.

added.title: Council of the Creek: Operation Hive-Mind
added.description: Hive Mind - When bees take over the Trading Tree, Craig must assemble the Council of the Creek to avert disaster.

added.title: The Bike Thief
added.description: Craig investigates the theft of the 10 Speed's bikes in hopes of finding the culprit!

added.title: Craig of the Beach
added.description: Craig gets to hit the beach with his friends and family, but starts to get worried his Dad is more fun than him.

added.title: Plush Kingdom
added.description: Craig, Kelsey, JP and Jessica discover a group of plushie obsessed kids, deep within the creek.

added.title: The Ice Pop Trio
added.description: Craig sets out in search of Ice Pops on a hot day with the help of an unlikely duo.

added.title: Pencil Break Mania
added.description: When Pencil Break Mania hits the Creek, JP finds himself as an unlikely champion and is forced to defend his title against the very best!

added.title: The Last Game of Summer
added.description: It's the last day of summer, and the last chance for Craig to uncover an ancient treasure beneath the Creek.

added.title: Trick or Creek
added.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: Craig finds himself being chased by a monster in the Creek that's straight out of the movies!

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: The Rise and Fall of the Green Poncho
added.description: Craig tries to warn his friends about the Other Side of the Creek with a tale from the Creek's defender - the Green Poncho.

added.title: I Don't Need a Hat
added.description: Craig decides to ditch his hat on a chilly day and it becomes a battle for body heat.

added.title: Alternate Creekiverse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP imagine a disturbing alternate reality where they never became friends!

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Craig and his friends desperately want a Snow Day, so they turn to the most powerful people they know... The Witches of the Creek!

added.title: Winter Break
added.description: Craig returns to the Creek after the long Winter Break only to find an empty wasteland and danger lurking in the snow.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: While taking refuge from the chilly Creek, Craig and his friends decide to hangout at his house until lunch time!

added.title: Breaking the Ice
added.description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

added.title: Winter Creeklympics
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP try their luck at winning Gold in their first ever, Winter Creeklympics!

added.title: Welcome to Creek Street
added.description: Craig and his friends create their own neighborhood in the snow!

added.title: Fan or Foe
added.description: When Elder Con comes to the Creek, Craig, Kelsey and JP each have a con experience they'll never forget.

added.title: New Jersey
added.description: After donning a brand new Jersey, JP is recruited by the Hockey Kids! The only way to get JP back is for Craig and Kelsey to hit the ice!

added.title: The Sunflower
added.description: Our Trio makes a new friend in the Creek, but when her pet befalls a tragic fate, Kelsey believes she knows how to help.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: Body Swap
added.description: Fed up with their home experiences, Craig, Kelsey and JP agree to switch bodies!

added.title: Copycat Carter
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon Carter, the cardboard genius turned cyborg, and Craig decides to help Carter become a kid again, just like him!

added.title: Brother Builder
added.description: As Craig races against time to build a super important invention, we learn how Craig became such a clever inventor!

added.title: Jessica the Intern
added.description: Entranced with the Trading Tree and Kit's business acumen, Jessica joins Kit as her intern!

added.title: Capture The Flag Part I
added.description: When mysterious circumstances cause issues at the Trading Tree, Craig tries to save the day!

added.title: Capture The Flag Part II
added.description: The Creek gets help from an unlikely friend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part III
added.description: Craig goes in search of answers, and finds a legend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part IV
added.description: Craig puts a plan into motion to save the Creek.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part V
added.description: It all comes down to this, the fate of the Creek is at stake!

added.title: Memories of Bobby
added.description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
added.description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

added.title: Kelsey the Elder
added.description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

added.title: Sour Candy Trials
added.description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

added.title: Fort Williams
added.description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

added.title: The Other Side
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP must journey past the Overpass into uncharted territory, the Other Side of the Creek.

added.title: Summer Wish
added.description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

added.title: Turning the Tables
added.description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

added.title: Kelsey the Author
added.description: Craig and Stacks help Kelsey become a real author turning her story into a book!

added.title: Council of the Creek
added.description: The circle game wreaks havoc on the Creek, so Craig forms a council to restore order.

added.title: Sparkle Cadet
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP team up with an intergalactic hero named Sparkle Cadet, hoping to save the Creek from negativity.

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: Creek Daycare
added.description: Craig and his sister, Jessica, try their hand at running the daycare at the Creek.

added.title: Sugar Smugglers
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP become smugglers to sneak candy to kids in need.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: Tea Timer's Ball
added.description: The Tea Timers throw a dance and invite everyone in the Creek. Craig believes it's solely to prank him, while Kelsey deals with an unwanted admirer.

added.title: The Cardboard Identity
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon a mysterious bunker made of cardboard beneath the Creek.

added.title: Ancients of the Creek
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP discover an ancient fort that belonged to the first kids in the Creek.

added.title: Mortimor to the Rescue
added.description: When Craig, Kelsey and JP get stranded in murky water, it's up to Mortimor to save the day!

added.title: Secret in a Bottle
added.description: Craig needs to get a secret off his chest, so he pays a visit to the Keeper of Secrets in the Creek.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: After Craig accidentally destroys a shipment of rare Chocorolls at the Trading Tree, Kit makes him work off his debt by running her trades throughout the Creek!

added.title: Crisis at Elder Rock
added.description: Tragedy strikes the Creek when the Elders get trapped under Elder Rock, and it's up to Craig, Kelsey and JP to rescue them.

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: The End Was Here
added.description: Craig tries to figure out how an ancient war that decimated the Creek began in hopes of stopping history from repeating itself.

added.title: In the Key of the Creek
added.description: When a rainy day keeps Craig inside, he uses his toys and imagination to create his own Creek adventure in Craig of the Creek's first musical episode!

added.title: Jessica Shorts
added.description: Spend some time with Craig's little sister, Jessica, as she trains to be the best video game fighter, deals with a loose tooth, puts on her own TV show, saves a sword and takes family game night too far.

added.title: Ferret Quest
added.description: The kids are on the search for an elusive ferret in the Creek.  Kelsey unites her friends Stacks and Wildernessa to find it, but worries they'd rather hangout with each other instead of her.

added.title: Into the Overpast
added.description: Craig and The Green Poncho travel to the Other Side of the Creek where Craig learns Green Poncho's shocking origin story.

added.title: The Time Capsule
added.description: Worried he'll one day forget all his favorite memories, Craig creates a time capsule to remember them all.

added.title: Beyond the Rapids
added.description: Resident creek scientist Wren enlists Craig to voyage through dangerous waters in search of a path to the Ocean.

added.title: The Jinxening
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP help a kid who's been jinxed and can't talk, but they soon come to regret it.

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Under the Overpass
added.description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

added.title: The Invitation
added.description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party.

added.title: Vulture's Nest
added.description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

added.title: Kelsey Quest
added.description: Kelsey accepts a quest from the Elders of the Creek, but is she ready for her terrifying opponent?

added.title: JPony
added.description: JP decides to follow his heart and tries to join the Horse Girls.

added.title: Ace of Squares
added.description: Craig vows to make the game of Four Square fun again by challenging its most dominant player!

added.title: Doorway to Helen
added.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

added.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
added.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Bug City
added.description: Craig discovers a bunch of bugs under a rock and decides to build them a city.

added.title: Deep Creek Salvage
added.description: The Trio finds gold in the muddy depths of the Creek so Craig builds a rig to recover it.

added.title: The Shortcut
added.description: An unusually hot day at the Creek melts all of Kit's ice pops, so Craig helps her find a short cut to her frozen snack supplier before everyone else melts.

added.title: Dibs Court
added.description: When a kid claims dibs on the Stump, Craig has no choice but to take them to court. Dibs Court.

added.title: The Great Fossil Rush
added.description: JP finds a fossil in the Creek which quickly causes the landscape to change.

added.title: The Mystery of the Timekeeper
added.description: When the Time Keeper goes missing, Craig and his friends take up the task of helping kids get home in time for dinner.

added.title: Alone Quest
added.description: Craig has an "emergency" leaving Kelsey alone at the Stump.

added.title: Recuerdos de Bobby
added.description: Cuando un importante miembro de la comunidad del Arroyo se marcha, el trío lamenta su pérdida recordando los buenos tiempos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Jacob del Arroyo
added.description: Un terrible corte de cabello obliga a Craig a visitar el Arroyo de encubierto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Regreso de los Guardabosques Madreselva
added.description: Craig descubre que los Guardabosques Madreselva se han infiltrado en su lado del Arroyo para robar su posesión más preciada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la Anciana
added.description: Una discusión entre los Ancianos del Arroyo deja un lugar vacante en su juego de rol de mesa, así que Kelsey se une a la campaña.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Craig se embarca en un alucinante viaje mientras trata de comer la golosina más ácida del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Fuerte Williams
added.description: iCuando Craig no puede ir al Arroyo, él y su madre deciden construir el fuerte de cobijas más grande del mundo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Otro Lado
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP deben viajar a través del Puente y aventurarse hacia el territorio no explorado del Otro Lado del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Deseo de Verano
added.description: Cuando Craig decide dejar una luciérnaga dentro de un frasco, termina interfiriendo con el delicado equilibrio del verano.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Craig almuerza en el restaurante donde trabaja su hermano mayor y pide un plato de VENGANZA… y muchos palitos de pan.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la autora
added.description: iCraig y Stacks ayudan a Kelsey a convertirse en una verdadera autora al convertir su historia en un libro!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El consejo del Arroyo
added.description: El juego del circulo siembra el caos en el Arroyo, así que Craig forma un consejo para restaurar el orden.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP forman equipo con una heroína intergaláctica llamada Cadete Destello, con la esperanza de salvar al Arroyo de la negatividad.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Primo del Arroyo
added.description: Craig lleva a su primo Bryson al Arroyo, donde accidentalmente inicia una guerra de globos de agua.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Campista Profuga
added.description: Una fugitiva de un campamento de verano termina en el Tronco, pero Craig sospecha que su historia puede no ser lo que parece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Evolucion de Craig
added.description: iCraig rescata a un renacuajo y decide criarlo hasta que sea una rana nivel 100!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Craig y la mesa de los ninos
added.description: Llegó el Día de Acción de Gracias de la familia Williams, iasí que es hora de reunir a la Mesa de los chicos! Pero cuando, por accidente, Bernard destruye el postre, Craig usa el poder de la Mesa de los chicos como ayuda para salvar a su hermano de un castigo asegurado.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Craig y el Poncho Verde viajan al otro lado del Arroyo, donde Craig conoce la impactante historia del origen del Poncho Verde.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La capsula del tiempo
added.description: Craig teme olvidar un día sus recuerdos favoritos, y por eso crea una cápsula del tiempo para recordarlos todos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: JP invita a sus amigos para una pijamada, pero resulta ser la misma noche que un gran juego con linternas en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La identidad de carton
added.description: Craig y sus amigos se topan con un refugio subterráneo hecho de cartón debajo del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la merecedora
added.description: Cuando Kelsey demuele una pared de la casa de Craig, su padre le quita la espada. Por eso, Kelsey les pide ayuda a Craig y a JP para que le demuestren a su padre que aún la merece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Mortimer al rescate
added.description: Cuando Craig, Kelsey y JP quedan varados en agua turbia, iMortimer debe salir al rescate!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La casa de munecas embrujada
added.description: Craig y sus amigos descubren que los persigue una muñeca aterradora y su casa de muñecas embrujada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Dia de trueque
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Craig destruye un cargamento de chocolates poco comunes en el árbol del trueque, Kit lo hace trabajar para pagar su deuda: idebe ocuparse de los intercambios de Kit por todo el bosque!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP se convierten en contrabandistas para llevarle dulces a niños necesitados.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Los Infusionistas organizan un baile e invitan a todos los habitantes del bosque. Craig cree que el único propósito del baile es hacerle una broma a él, mientras que Kelsey debe lidiar con un admirador indeseado.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El secreto en la botella
added.description: Craig necesita compartir un secreto con alguien, por lo que visita al Guardián de los Secretos en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Crisis en la roca de Ancianos
added.description: Una tragedia azota al Arroyo cuando los Ancianos quedan atrapados bajo la Roca Anciana. Ahora Craig, Kelsey y JP deben rescatarlos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Guarderia del Arroyo
added.description: Craig y su hermana Jessica intentan administrar la guarderia del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Llego el final
added.description: Craig intenta comprender cómo se desató una antigua antigua que diezmó la población del Arroyo, con la esperanza de evitar que la historia se repita.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Ancianos de arroyo
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP descubren una fortaleza antigua que les perteneció a los primeros niños del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Ganas de Explorar
added.description: La misión de Craig de mapear el Arroyo entero los lleva a él y a sus amigos a arboleda traicionera de Hiedra Venenosa
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Traes
added.description: Un despiadado juego de persecución desata un caos en el Arroyo, y se declara a Kelsey como la próxima perseguidora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Jessica va al Arroyo
added.description: Cuando Craig y Jessica quedan encerrados fuera de la casa, Craig no tiene otra opción: debe llevar a su hermanita al Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Libro Final
added.description: El último libro de fantasía de la serie favorita de Kelsey desaparece de la biblioteca. Por eso, Craig decide ayudarla a resolver el misterio de quién se lo llevó.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Demasiados Tesoros
added.description: Con la esperanza de reparar su fuerte, Craig consigue la ayuda de Los Veloces Diez para llevarlos hasta la legendaria pila de basura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Salvajessa
added.description: Un encuentro con Salvajessa, guardiana de la naturaleza, inspira a Kelsey a dedicarse a una causa.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Ropa Dominguera
added.description: JP ensucia su última ropa limpia y debe ponerse su mejor ropa de domingo para ir al arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Escape de la Cena Familiar
added.description: En el arroyo se disputa una enorme pelea con globos acuáticos, pero Craig está atrapado en la cena familiar, a menos que pueda escapar.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Monstruo en el Jardin
added.description: Craig está decidido a atrapar al monstruo que ha estado desatando un caos en el jardín del abuelo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Maldicion
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP entran en conflicto con unas brujas adolescentes deshonestas, ique les lanzan una maldición! iQué adolescentes malvadas!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Perro Decisivo
added.description: Incapaz de tomar decisiones difíciles, Craig decide poner sus decisiones en manos de un perro llamado Fred.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Saca tu Bestia
added.description: Craig quiere jugar a un popular juego de cartas, así que decide tomar prestadas las cartas antiguas y valiosas de Bernard.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Perdidos en la Cloaca
added.description: Craig acepta ayudar a la Reina de las Alcantarillas a trazar el mapa de las alcantarillas, pero rápidamente se encuentra en una situación que lo supera.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El futuro es de Carton
added.description: Los niños conocen a un excéntrico Creador de Cartón que invita a Craig a ayudarlo a terminar su obra maestra.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: La determinación de Craig de conseguirle a su abuelo un caparazón de cigarra hace que él, Kelsey y JP queden atrapados en su tronco.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.description: Craig y sus amigos viajan para encontrar madreselva en el arroyo, pero descubren una parte completamente nueva del arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Invitacion
added.description: Craig y sus amigos están invitados a una exclusiva merienda con deliciosos postres, si es que pueden quedarse hasta el final de la fiesta.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Nido de buitres
added.description: Craig y sus amigos forman una banda, pero a Craig lo atormenta una pesadilla aterradora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La aventura de Kelsey
added.description: Kelsey acepta una misión de los Ancianos del Arroyo, pero ¿está lista para su aterrador rival?

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Cena en el Arroyo

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Buscando a Jessica

added.title: Ciudad de bichos

added.title: El Atajo

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Tronco es mio

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Gran Fiebre de Fosiles

added.title: El Misterio de la Guardiana del Tiempo

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Mision solitaria

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Nia's Perfect Plan

added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Something to Remember
added.description: On the last day of Yong Bao's visit to Sodor, his friends dig up a giant keepsake to help him remember them.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Voosh
added.description: Bing is vooshing with Hoppity around the garden, and Hoppity is vooshing higher and higher. But what happens when Hoppity vooshes so high that he disappears?

added.title: Nature Explorer
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: Elly's Computer
added.description: Elly is playing with her computer, which has a screen, a mouse and a keyboard, while Pocoyo waits to play ball with her. Pocoyo gets angry because Elly isn't playing with him, but then Elly finishes her videogame and they can finally go out and play ball together.

added.title: Going to the Beach
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato receive a postcard from Elly, who is on vacation at the beach. Not to be outdone, they set up their own beach. All ready with their sunglasses, a bucket and shovel, they build a fantastic sandcastle. Now they just have to wait for Elly to get back so they can all play at their beach together.

added.title: Big and Small
added.description: Pocoyo is playing with a remote control that makes things big and small. He turns Pato's tower into a tiny tower, and Loula's bone and Elly's doll into gigantic objects. In the end, seeing how his friends all get upset, Pocoyo turns each thing back to its original size.

added.title: Pocoyo's Supermarket
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato have a supermarket. Elly calls them to order a bottle, which Pocoyo puts into a basket and delivers to her. Elly calls again to order a box and then a can. After several orders, Pocoyo and Pato are exhausted. Finally, Elly writes out a shopping list so that they can deliver everything at once with their cart.

added.title: Elly's Playhouse
added.description: Elly has a playhouse to play in. Her house has a door, a roof and a window. But when Pocoyo and Pato play with her, the playhouse comes down. With Elly's help, they manage to put it back together, placing everything back in its place.

added.title: Face Painting
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato are drawing pictures, and Elly wants them to draw her new doll. So they draw a picture of the eyes, another of the nose, another of the mouth and two drawings of the ears. To keep Elly from getting angry, they decide to put together a giant picture with all the parts of the doll.
